---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Code Structure Navigation - SqueezyAgent"
  description="Draft code-structure navigation docs for SqueezyAgent."
  activeDoc="/docs/semantic-navigation/"
  heading="Code structure navigation"
  lead="The core cost-saving bet is simple: ask local code structure before paying the model to search text."
>
  <section class="doc-block">
    <span class="status-pill">pre-v0 placeholder</span>
    <h2>Rust first</h2>
    <p>
      Rust is the first supported source language for structure-aware
      navigation. The local engine should cover files, declarations, imports,
      references, call-like syntax, test pairing, and Cargo facts.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Clear limits</h2>
    <p>
      Static analysis can quickly find useful structure, but it should not
      pretend every relationship is certain. When local structure is incomplete,
      SqueezyAgent should say so and use bounded text search as a fallback.
    </p>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
